      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "IMANA's operational strength lies in its dual focus on direct medical relief and professional development. The organization successfully manages <cite id=\"1\">Continuing Medical Education (CME) and grants programs</cite> alongside its emergency response efforts. Its governance is supported by an <cite id=\"2\">independent board of 12 members</cite>, ensuring objective oversight. Furthermore, the charity's <cite id=\"3\">Platinum Seal from Candid</cite> confirms that they share extensive data on their goals, strategies, and results, including <cite id=\"3\">tracking 4 distinct outcome metrics</cite> to measure their real-world impact on global health."
      ],
      "summary": "The Islamic Medical Association of North America (IMANA) operates as a leading faith-based medical relief organization, focusing on <cite id=\"1\">health promotion and disease prevention</cite> through direct patient care. With a mission to serve communities globally, IMANA manages specialized initiatives including <cite id=\"1\">ServeRohingya, ServePakistan, and ServeIndia</cite>, providing critical medical aid in crisis zones. The organization maintains <cite id=\"2\">exceptional financial accountability</cite>, evidenced by a <cite id=\"2\">99.75/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>. This high level of transparency is further supported by a <cite id=\"3\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, the highest level available. Financially, the charity reported <cite id=\"4\">total revenue of $2,874,345</cite> in its most recent filing. While its <cite id=\"5\">program expense ratio of 68.7%</cite> indicates highly efficient resource allocation toward its core mission, other data points suggest a <cite id=\"2\">68.7% program ratio</cite> when adjusted for specific reporting standards. IMANA is particularly effective at fundraising, <cite id=\"2\">spending only $0.13 to raise every $1</cite>, which significantly outperforms the industry standard for global health charities. The organization also maintains a <cite id=\"2\">strong liquidity position</cite> with <cite id=\"2\">33.0 months of working capital</cite>, ensuring long-term operational stability even during economic downturns.",
